Description: Floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup; turn of broad foot just preserved; glazed black on interior and exterior; exterior: scraped groove at junction with stem; inscription cut on interior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 531)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 675, no. 340)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1623)
